<p>How to realize a function that takes as input an any number of procedures with one argument and returns another function is the composition of these procedures in Scheme.</p>  <p>For example:</p>  <pre><code>(define (f x) (* x 2)) (define (g x) (* x 3)) (define (h x) (- x))  ((comp-func f g h) 1) =&gt; -6 ((comp-func f g) 1)   =&gt; 6 ((comp-func h) 1)     =&gt; -1 ((comp-func) 1)       =&gt; 1 </code></pre>